    public static double calculateDistanceTraveled(List<GPSLocation> polyline) {
        double totalDistance = 0.0;

        for (int i = 1; i < polyline.size(); i++) {
            double lat1 = Math.toRadians(polyline.get(i - 1).getLat());
            double lon1 = Math.toRadians(polyline.get(i - 1).getLng());
            double lat2 = Math.toRadians(polyline.get(i).getLat());
            double lon2 = Math.toRadians(polyline.get(i).getLng());

            double dlon = lon2 - lon1;
            double dlat = lat2 - lat1;

            double a = Math.pow(Math.sin(dlat / 2), 2) + Math.cos(lat1) * Math.cos(lat2) * Math.pow(Math.sin(dlon / 2), 2);
            double c = 2 * Math.atan2(Math.sqrt(

a), Math.sqrt(1 - a));

            double distance = 6371 * c; // Radius of the Earth in kilometers

            totalDistance += distance;
        }

        return totalDistance;
    }
}
```

The `calculateDistanceTraveled` function iterates through the list of GPS coordinates and calculates the distance between consecutive points using the Haversine formula, which takes into account the curvature of the Earth. The distances are then summed up to obtain the total distance traveled by the vehicle.

